{"body": "@NZKoz sorry, I'm learning here, so please bear with me...\r\nSay instead we add a preliminary call:\r\n- 1st call: Pre-login call to get csrf token\r\n- 2nd call: Login with auth details and verify with csrf token\r\n- 3rd call: use session cookies to perform logged in action\r\n\r\nWould that not provide the same security as a browser? What's the benefit of an API token over this? \r\n\r\nAlso, you say sessions for an API are \"horribly wrong\", but _why_? Why do we need to be treating non-browser clients differently to browsers? They're both just clients between the user and the site.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14083556", "created_at": "2013-02-25T23:37:21Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9405#issuecomment-14083556", "updated_at": "2013-02-25T23:37:49Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9405, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/Dan2552", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/51f5b50028b4d67725f4ad18170a5066?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F2945baa5c102a460bd804b69dc01e591.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/received_events", "gravatar_id": "51f5b50028b4d67725f4ad18170a5066", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "Dan2552", "type": "User", "id": 1478221, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dan2552/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ea3ebd3543c151009983"}, "id": 14083556, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rail